column1: DESCRIPTION:Spoke to Scott Meyers.\nGovernment-specific: HotDocs. Takes Word documents and makes templates out of them. Insurance and banking / governments. Good for filling out the same documents on a regular basis. Easy to change and update. Best for formal
column2: legal-esque stuff. Doesn't have a partner program or anything. Familiar with us. He's normally the guy we'd work with. Shaz / Norman. Global company
column3: no particular office in the region. HQ in San Diego. He's in Utah. \nLikes virtual work.\nShoot him an email so he has your contact.

column1: SUMMARY:Outbound call Acces I/O Products Inc.
DESCRIPTION:Val in sales responded to call
column2:
sent me over to Bob (her supervisor). 
They don't have any sort of partner program but we can open an account with them to get perks and discounts on purchases that might increase our margins. 
We worked for a while to find the order number relating our companies from the RFQ. We had apparently started to set up an account with them at some point but had not finished. 
They have a guy from Georgia who sometimes comes up near DC if we were interested in meeting. Kevin Wall.

column1: DESCRIPTION:John responded to the call. Ryan no longer works there.\nABMX sells servers and fully-assembled systems. \nLast sale in July of last year. Don't really do lead generation / contract stuff. Lead generation from Google

column1: DESCRIPTION:James Guerrero answered the phone. EnviroSafety is a child company of Guardian Safety.\nIn CA. Discussed an email and where we might like to meet in the future. His email is jguerrero@envirosafety.com.
